<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>ViralScan Report</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --brand: #2563eb;
      --brand-light: #eff6ff;
      --warn:  #b45309;
      --warn-light: #fffbeb;
      --ok:    #15803d;
      --ok-light: #f0fdf4;
      --border: #e2e8f0;
      --text:  #1e293b;
      --muted: #64748b;
      --radius: 8px;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); background: #f8fafc; }
    header {
      background: var(--brand); color: #fff;
      padding: 2rem 3rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    header h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; }
    header p  { opacity: 0.85; margin-top: 0.25rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    main { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem 4rem; }
    section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--brand);
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .card {
      background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .meta-grid {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    .meta-grid dt { color: var(--muted); }
    .meta-grid dd { font-weight: 500; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.88rem; }
    th { background: var(--brand-light); color: var(--brand);
         text-align: left; padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); }
    td { padding: 0.45rem 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    tr:hover td { background: #f1f5f9; }
    .badge {
      display: inline-block; padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
      border-radius: 999px; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600;
    }
    .badge-found   { background: var(--ok-light);   color: var(--ok); }
    .badge-none    { background: #f1f5f9; color: var(--muted); }
    .badge-high    { background: var(--warn-light); color: var(--warn); }
    .alert {
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: var(--radius);
      font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .alert-ok   { background: var(--ok-light);   border-left: 4px solid var(--ok);   color: var(--ok); }
    .alert-none { background: #f1f5f9;            border-left: 4px solid var(--muted); color: var(--muted); }
    .alert-info { background: var(--brand-light); border-left: 4px solid var(--brand); color: var(--brand); }
    .plots-grid {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(340px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem;
    }
    .plot-card {
      background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden;
    }
    .plot-card p { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); padding: 0.4rem 0.75rem; }
    .plot-card img { width: 100%; display: block; }
    footer {
      text-align: center; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted);
      padding: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 3rem;
    }
    .number { font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>ViralScan Report</h1>
  <p>Generated {{ run_date }} &nbsp;·&nbsp; Output: {{ output_dir }}</p>
</header>

<main>

  <!-- ── Run metadata ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section>
    <h2>Run Summary</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <dl class="meta-grid">
        <dt>Viruses detected</dt>
        <dd class="number">{{ total_viruses }}</dd>
        <dt>Infected cells (any virus)</dt>
        <dd class="number">{{ per_cell_count }}</dd>
        <dt>Detection threshold</dt>
        <dd>≥ {{ detection_threshold }} viral UMI</dd>
        <dt>Super-expressor threshold</dt>
        <dd>≥ {{ se_threshold }} UMI/cell</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>

    {% if any_infected %}
    <div class="alert alert-ok">
      ✓ &nbsp; Viral reads were detected. See the tables below for details.
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <div class="alert alert-none">
      ✗ &nbsp; No viral reads above the detection threshold were found in this sample.
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </section>

  <!-- ── Per-virus statistics ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section>
    <h2>Per-Virus Statistics</h2>
    {% if virus_stats %}
    <div class="card" style="padding: 0; overflow: hidden;">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Virus</th>
            <th>Total UMI</th>
            <th>Infected cells</th>
            <th>Total cells</th>
            <th>% Infected</th>
            <th>UMI / 10k</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for virus, s in virus_stats.items() %}
          <tr>
            <td>
              {% if s.infected_cells > 0 %}
              <span class="badge badge-found">{{ virus }}</span>
              {% else %}
              <span class="badge badge-none">{{ virus }}</span>
              {% endif %}
            </td>
            <td class="number">{{ s.total_umi }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ s.infected_cells }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ s.total_cells }}</td>
            <td class="number">
              {% if s.pct_infected > 1.0 %}
              <span class="badge badge-high">{{ "%.2f"|format(s.pct_infected) }}%</span>
              {% else %}
              {{ "%.2f"|format(s.pct_infected) }}%
              {% endif %}
            </td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.2f"|format(s.umi_per_10k) }}</td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="alert alert-info" style="margin-top:0.75rem; font-size:0.82rem;">
      <strong>Metrics:</strong>
      <em>UMI / 10k</em> = total viral UMI ÷ total sample UMI × 10,000 (analogous to CPM/TPM, normalises for library size).
      <em>% Infected</em> = fraction of cells with ≥ {{ detection_threshold }} viral UMI.
    </div>

    {% else %}
    <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">No viruses detected.</p>
    {% endif %}
  </section>

  <!-- ── Multimapping evidence ───────────────────────────────────── -->
  {% if multimap_evidence %}
  <section>
    <h2>Multimapping Evidence</h2>
    <div class="card" style="padding: 0; overflow: hidden;">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Virus</th>
            <th>Gene ID</th>
            <th>Unique UMI</th>
            <th>Ambiguous UMI</th>
            <th>Host-virus ambiguous</th>
            <th>Corrected UMI</th>
            <th>Confidence</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for row in multimap_evidence %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ row.virus_name }}</td>
            <td><code>{{ row.gene_id }}</code></td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.3g"|format(row.unique_viral_umi) }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.3g"|format(row.ambiguous_viral_umi) }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.3g"|format(row.host_viral_ambiguous_umi) }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.3g"|format(row.corrected_viral_umi) }}</td>
            <td>{{ row.call_confidence }}</td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="alert alert-info" style="margin-top:0.75rem; font-size:0.82rem;">
      Multimapper method: <strong>{{ multimap_method }}</strong>;
      primary call policy: <strong>{{ multimap_primary_call }}</strong>.
      Host-virus ambiguous UMI are compatible with both host and viral genes and should be interpreted cautiously.
    </div>
  </section>
  {% endif %}

  <!-- ── Detected virus names ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  {% if detected_viruses %}
  <section>
    <h2>Detected Viruses (official names)</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul style="list-style: disc inside; font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        {% for v in detected_viruses %}
        <li>{{ v }}</li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
  {% endif %}

  <!-- ── Cell-type enrichment ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  {% if cell_type_enrichment %}
  <section>
    <h2>Cell-Type Enrichment</h2>
    <div class="card" style="padding: 0; overflow: hidden;">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Virus</th>
            <th>Cell type</th>
            <th>Infected</th>
            <th>Total</th>
            <th>% Infected</th>
            <th>Odds ratio</th>
            <th>p-value</th>
            <th>BH padj</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for row in cell_type_enrichment %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ row.virus }}</td>
            <td>{{ row.cell_type }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ row.n_infected }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ row.n_total }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.2f"|format(row.pct) }}%</td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.3g"|format(row.OR) }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.3g"|format(row.pvalue) }}</td>
            <td class="number">{{ "%.3g"|format(row.padj) }}</td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="alert alert-info" style="margin-top:0.75rem; font-size:0.82rem;">
      One-sided Fisher exact test (alternative="greater") per cell type versus all other labeled cells.
      padj uses Benjamini-Hochberg FDR correction across tested rows.
    </div>
  </section>
  {% endif %}

  <!-- ── Plots ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  {% if embedded_plots %}
  <section>
    <h2>Visualisations</h2>
    <div class="plots-grid">
      {% for fname, b64 in embedded_plots.items() %}
      <div class="plot-card">
        <img src="data:image/png;base64,{{ b64 }}" alt="{{ fname }}" loading="lazy" />
        <p>{{ fname }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </section>
  {% endif %}

  <!-- ── Interpretation guide ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section>
    <h2>Interpretation Guide</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Key metrics explained</h3>
      <dl style="font-size:0.88rem; line-height:1.7;">
        <dt style="font-weight:600;">UMI / 10k (viral load per library)</dt>
        <dd style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
          Normalises total viral UMI by total sample UMI × 10,000 — comparable across samples with
          different sequencing depths.  A value &gt; 1 indicates meaningful viral signal.
        </dd>
        <dt style="font-weight:600;">% Infected cells</dt>
        <dd style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
          Fraction of all droplets containing ≥ {{ detection_threshold }} viral UMI.
          Because ambient RNA can contaminate droplets, values &lt; 0.1% should be interpreted
          cautiously without further decontamination (e.g. SoupX/DecontX).
        </dd>
        <dt style="font-weight:600;">Super-expressors</dt>
        <dd style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
          Cells with ≥ {{ se_threshold }} viral UMI in the super-expressor plot.  These are
          candidate productively infected cells.  The null model (grey line) shows the expected
          distribution if viral reads were distributed proportionally to total cell UMI.
        </dd>
        <dt style="font-weight:600;">Nearest-neighbour enrichment</dt>
        <dd>
          Computed in the UMAP step (if run).  Tests whether virus-positive cells cluster in
          transcriptomic space beyond chance (permutation p-value shown in the UMAP annotation).
          Significant clustering (p &lt; 0.05) suggests true infection rather than ambient contamination.
        </dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Output files ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section>
    <h2>Output Files</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>summary.txt</code></td><td>Plain-text summary (legacy, human-readable)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>results/viral_summary.tsv</code></td><td>Per-virus statistics table (TSV)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>results/per_cell_viral.tsv</code></td><td>Per-barcode viral UMI annotation (TSV)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>results/multimap_evidence.tsv</code></td><td>Unique and ambiguous viral evidence table (TSV)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>plots/</code></td><td>UMI bar plots and super-expressor scatter plots (PNG)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>plots/umap_binary.html</code></td><td>Interactive UMAP coloured by virus (if --umap)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>plots/umap_continuous.html</code></td><td>Interactive UMAP coloured by viral load (if --umap)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>kb-python/</code></td><td>Raw kallisto|bustools count matrices</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

<footer>
  Generated by <strong>ViralScan</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; {{ run_date }}
</footer>

</body>
</html>
